dismissalText.commentary: Mushfiqur Rahim c Rahane b Parvez Rasool 59 (63b 3x4 3x6 70m) SR: 93.65

dismissalComment.html: Rasool has another wicket. Mushfiq looks to target Rasool again, but this time he is not close to the potch of the ball even though he has stepped outside the crease. Gets a massive edge on this, and Rahane completes a safe catch in the mid-off area

dismissalText.commentary: Shakib Al Hasan c & b Raina 52 (58b 4x4 1x6 75m) SR: 89.65

dismissalComment.html: Coolly Raina takes the big wicket of Shakib. The batsman wants to pull this shortish delivery, but it stops on him, and he ends up hitting this straight back at Raina which catches it with fingers pointing skywards

first wicket of the series. Tamim's edgy innings ends. He is squared up by this shortish delivery that angles across him. Seems to have kissed the outside edge on the way. Well actually it hasn't. The bat hit the pad at the same time as the ball passed the bat, creating the misleading noise. Tamim has had a rough one here
Mominul never looked in. He is out now. On a length, angling away, and a lazy loose drive from Mominul. Feet stuck, bat speed slow, playing away from the body, and a soft edge through to Saha

dismissalComment.html: there is life in this dog yet. Ziaur Rahamn, who was rather slow in diving a ball ago, flies at short third man to send Rahane back. commentTextItems.html: India win. Short of a length, just outside off, he makes room and cuts this past point to seal off the chase

commentPostTextItems.html: That's that then. Good night and good luck

"Pleased with especially Robin and Ajju," says Suresh Raina. "Very happy with the bowlers, especially Rasool and Akshar. And obviously Mishra. It was very tough for the bowlers in these conditions. Both fast bowlers were cramping up. The toughest conditions we have bowled in, in terms of the heat. Robin has been batting well, and Ajju is one of the cleanest batsmen I have seen."

"After looking at that wicket I think we were 20 short," says Mushfiqur Rahim. "But they batted really well, especially in the first 10 overs. Our bowlers also gave away loose balls. Their bowlers didn't do that. Decision at the toss can go either way. As I said this was a young Indian side. Had we got those 20 extra runs..."

"Really happy," says Ajinkya Rahane, the Man of the Match. "The start is really important for any series. The partnership at the top was crucial, but the bowlers did really well in that heat. It was really challenging. We just wanted to give our 100%. We thought they were 15-20 short. The credit goes to the bowlers."

India were cruising when the rain arrived, but on resumption they were left a banana skin of target: 50 off 56. They lost a wicket immediately, but Ajinkya Rahane, who along with Robin Uthappa staked a claim for the regular opening slot, sealed the chase with a cool fifty
Bangladesh will look back at their batting - especially their inability to take singles regularly in the first 25 overs of the innings - and will see that is where they lost the match

commentTextItems.html: Raina does it coolly. Down the wicket, under the ball, drives this wide of long-off for four
driven down to long-on for a single
turning down leg, Mushfiqur appeals for a catch. He doesn't get the call, but it is not called a wide either

commentPreTextItems.html: Mahmudullah to bowl the 25th over. Can Bangladesh take this into the final over

commentTextItems.html: arm ball, on off, punched wide of the man at point for a single
slower ball, short of a length, and Rayudu sets off again when there is no single available and it is Raina's call. Hit straight to point
low full toss, he is down the wicket, pushes this wide of extra cover, and gets a single because of Anamul's dive
on a length, middle and leg, defended to midwicket
on a length, middle and leg, defended to midwicket
Raina gets lucky. Short ball, on off, he pulls, gets a bottom edge that beats the stumps and the keeper
on a length, outside off, driven past point for a single
short of a length, pitched outside leg, defended back to Mortaza
short of a length, just outside leg, angling towards off, and he is hit high on the pad. The ball has gone nowhere, but Rayudu still wants a leg-bye. Crazy runner he is
short, wide, pushed straight to cover
short of a length, into the pads, worked to leg for one

commentPreTextItems.html: Raina has come in to bat

commentTextItems.html: on a length, on off, pushed to mid-off for one

beaten in the flight as he looks to step out. Pushes in front of the body to defend

dismissalText.commentary: Shakib Al Hasan c & b Raina 52 (58b 4x4 1x6 75m) SR: 89.65

dismissalComment.html: Coolly Raina takes the big wicket of Shakib. The batsman wants to pull this shortish delivery, but it stops on him, and he ends up hitting this straight back at Raina which catches it with fingers pointing skywards

headshotImage.caption: Amit Mishra player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Amit Mishra player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Mahmudullah b Mishra 41 (44b 6x4 0x6 61m) SR: 93.18

dismissalComment.html: Mishra gets his own back. His flatter legbreak that doesn't turn much. Just enough top beat the defensive bat of Mahmudullah, and pegs back the off stump

dismissalText.commentary: Ziaur Rahman c Raina b Yadav 2 (3b 0x4 0x6 4m) SR: 66.66

dismissalComment.html: superb catch by Raina. Zia tries to go over mid-off, mis-hits this completely, Raina runs in from straight extra cover, puts in the dive, and gets his right hand under it inches before it touches the ground

headshotImage.caption: Amit Mishra player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Amit Mishra player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Nasir Hossain c Rahane b Mishra 22 (20b 4x4 0x6 24m) SR: 110

dismissalComment.html: another wicket falls. Bangladesh falling apart here. This is tossed up wide outside off, Hossain is shaping up to slog-sweep, but the width makes him go into the off side. No control over the shot. Caught at long-off

headshotImage.caption: Axar Patel player page headshot cutout 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Axar Patel player page headshot cutout 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Mashrafe Mortaza b Patel 18 (10b 2x4 1x6 16m) SR: 180

dismissalComment.html: Patel's first international wicket. Mortaza goes back to make room to hit this over extra cover. is beaten by it, and the off stump is pegged back

dismissalComment.html: given out lbw but Uthappa half-shows him the bat, and rightly so. This is angled in from Shakib, but Uthappa has got a huge inside edge onto the pad. He has to go, though

dismissalText.long: c Ziaur Rahman b Mashrafe Mortaza
dismissalText.commentary: Ajinkya Rahane c Ziaur Rahman b Mashrafe Mortaza 64 (70b 5x4 2x6 93m) SR: 91.42

dismissalComment.html: there is life in this dog yet. Ziaur Rahamn, who was rather slow in diving a ball ago, flies at short third man to send Rahane back. Slower ball from Mortaza, Rahane drives, looking to go over extra, but gets a thick edge, and Zia takes it overhead when the ball has almost passed him

dismissalText.commentary: Cheteshwar Pujara lbw b Shakib Al Hasan 0 (5b 0x4 0x6 5m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: was an exactly similar delivery but this time Pujara has been given. This seems to be a direct result of the pressure from the previous delivery. This is even higher than the previous one. Can't see how that can be given. Great delivery but this is sailing over the stumps. Pujara's second duck in two innings
